Raspberries have significantly high levels of antioxidant compounds play potential role against ageing, inflammation and scavenge harmful free radicals. Let me explain what free-radicals are: these particles are part of a large group of atoms, molecules or ions that have one or more single electrons. These particles try to steal electrons from anything they bump into, including you! When a free-radical successfully steals an electron it causes oxidative damage and that leads to lines, wrinkles and aging in general. Anti-aging antioxidants stop free radicals from stealing electrons from your skin making it look brighter and younger. Raspberry has an ORAC value (oxygen radical absorbance capacity) of about 4900 µmol TE per 100 grams, crediting it among the top-ranked ORAC fruits.
